
[1]civilly

   CIVILLY, adv.

   1. In a manner relating to government, or to the rights or character of
   a member of the community.

   2. In a manner relating to private rights; opposed to criminally; as a
   process civilly commenced for the private satisfaction of a party
   injured.

   3. Not naturally, but in law; as a man civilly dead.

   4. Politely; complaisantly; gently; with due decorum; courteously; as,
   we were civilly treated.

   5. Without gaudy colors, or finery; as chambers furnished civilly.
